@sinkietemplatelife actually we know CFR. What we don’t yet know is the IFR — infection fatality rate. Only widespread antibody testing will show that. Given that there are 90-odd such tests on the US, some of which are inaccurate and unrealizable, which has in fact created a distrust of them, we will have to wait a bit. But wherever this has been done many more people have been found to have Covid already and self recovered. Which means the denominator (number of people actually infected) is magnitudes larger. Which means the fatality rate is actually much lower. Time will tell. For now people seem to prefer being fearful because...risk aversion to the point of stupidity. Thanks for the dialogue.

@sinkietemplatelife spikes happen in various clusters. It’s impractical and expensive to pre empty every possible cluster. Dorms are not the only ones, there could be others where life situation could lead to an outbreak. The important thing is how swiftly and comprehensively a government responds. SG has some exceptionally well, given fatality and critical care numbers. People keep misunderstanding what “new cases” means. It’s not an issue for people to catch this new strain in and of itself; if 99 out of 100 self recover (as antibody is telling us with IFR instead of CFR) what’s the problem? The virus isn’t going anywhere. Those who wish to stay home can and should stay home. This is no reason to crater the economy.

@sinkietemplatelife the purpose of the lockdown was to keep hospital infra protected. That has been achieved. At this point the economy should open. The media fascination with reporting “new cases” as of thats of huge concern is stupid. Young people which constitute majority of the economy should be back to work with new codes of conduct like masks. Vulnerable should remain in isolation.

@nearlynormal agree, we will never know the true CFR, as much the mortality rate is really far lower than it seems. There's no reason to prolong the economic and psychological strain on the country any longer

@sinkietemplatelife given the 20,000 plus cases and the minor count of fatalities of mostly senior and comorbid citizens and the low strain on critical hospital infrastructure this is not “mismanaged” by any stretch. People keep misunderstanding what a lockdown or CB is supposed to do. The virus won’t magically disappear.
